  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legal definitions typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing funds as seemingly legitimate income\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most involve:\n- Knowingly concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Attempting to disguise the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Engaging in financial transactions designed to hide money's illegal source\n\nMost jurisdictions classify money laundering as a criminal offense with potential penalties including:\n- Substantial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Prison sentences\n\nSpecific details and exact definitions can differ between countries and legal systems.",
